---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Animations">
  <h1>Animations</h1>
  <p>
    The six motion metaphors. Each communicates something specific — no ambient drift, no
    decorative motion.
  </p>

  <h2>Snapping</h2>
  <p>
    Hex slides into place over <code>--hp-unfold-trigger</code> (90ms). Used by
    <code>&lt;hp-grid&gt;</code> when a dragged hex releases onto its target slot.
  </p>

  <h2>Routing</h2>
  <p>
    Three trapezoidal segments draw along alternating hex edges, staggered by
    <code>--hp-unfold-stagger</code> (60ms). The trace is the focus indicator on any
    interactive <code>&lt;hp-cell&gt;</code> — it grows in on
    <code>:focus-visible</code> and unwinds in reverse on blur.
  </p>

  <h2>Hue swap</h2>
  <p>
    Blue → green on hover/focus across every interactive atom. Tied to
    <code>--hp-duration-medium</code> (280ms) so it reads as deliberate rather than instant.
  </p>

  <h2>Pulse</h2>
  <p>
    The only ambient motion the system allows — a dot travelling along an active
    <code>&lt;hp-tether&gt;</code> arc to signal "this connection is live". <em>Note:</em> pulse is
    currently off pending a redesign — the directed arrow carries directedness for now.
  </p>

  <h2>Bloom</h2>
  <p>
    Children appear staggered around a source hex during an unfold. <code>&lt;hp-unfold-list&gt;</code>
    when shipped will play this on toggle.
  </p>

  <h2>Scanning</h2>
  <p>
    Skeleton sweep for loading states; vertical lift for masked overflow. Both pending dedicated
    atoms.
  </p>
</Layout>
